The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, April 22, 2004 				 HCL Info bottomline flat
																								New Delhi, April 21 (PTI): HCL Infosystems today posted a flat consolidated net profit of Rs 55.47 crore in the third quarter ended March 2004 against Rs 55.64 crore in the year-ago period, owing to a deferred tax element.																								The flat or the 0.3 per cent marginal decline in net profit during the quarter was due to a Rs 25.64 crore deferred tax element in the previous third quarter.																								On a consolidated basis, the companys revenues were up 60.45 per cent at Rs 1,192.47 crore in the reporting quarter. HCL Infosystems announced a third interim dividend of 60 per cent for the quarter.																								This has been a satisfying quarter for us on multiple fronts. Our business grew robust in all areas... The governments initiative in encouraging PC manufacturing by lowering the taxes resulted in increasing volumes, said Ajai Chowdhry, chairman and CEO. 
